        "project-description": "This web app uses data from public *Yahoo Finance APIs* to train a *Random Forest Classifier* (~57% accuracy) built in *Python* to predict whether the *S&P 500 closing price* will rise or fall based on daily, weekly, and monthly trends, leveraging *scikit-learn, pandas, NumPy, and yfinance* for modeling and data processing; the backend was developed with *FastAPI*, the frontend with *React*, a *Redis cache* was implemented to efficiently serve daily predictions, and the entire system was deployed on a *self-configured home lab* using *Kubernetes* with a fully automated *CI/CD pipeline.*",
